The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 June is 42,583 (4,928.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 June, there were 227 new confirmed cases (26.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 May, there were 101 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 125% (126 extra cases).
